  2799                                  ;
  2800                                  ;       INT 30h Operating System Software Service Interrupt
  2801                                  ;
  2802                                  ;       Interrupt 30h is used by our operating system as an entry point for many commonly-used subroutines reusable by
  2803                                  ;       any task. These routines include low-level i/o functions that shield applications from having to handle
  2804                                  ;       device-specific communications. On entry to this interrupt, AL contains a function number that is used to load
  2805                                  ;       the entry address of the specific function from a table.
  2806                                  ;
  2807                                  ;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
